<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>Electrical System Troubleshooting Guide - BE 200, CE 200, CE 300 Model - LIGHT SYSTEMS - CLEARANCE LIGHTS -
        EXTENDED DESCRIPTION
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>EXTENDED DESCRIPTION</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08290_359.xml" xrefid="f082901109">Clearance Lights</hotlnk>.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Roof Clearance and Marker Lights</title>
            <para>When the ESC is commanded to turn the clearance lights on, the ESC will provide 12 volts to the
                clearance lights relay from ESC connector (1603) terminal H. When the relay is charged voltage from fuse
                #2 will then power the clearance lights through circuits 16YEL 2 and 16 YEL 51.
            </para>
            <para>The ground circuit path is from the ground stud on the flasher plate through circuit 16 WHT 1 and 16
                WHT 2 to individual ground circuits splitting out to the lights.
            </para>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
